  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how TripStudio ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use our mobile application (the "App").</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>When you use TripStudio, we may collect the following types of information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>User-Generated Content:</strong> Photos, videos, events, and itineraries that you upload.</li>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> If you sign in or create an account, we may collect your email address or username.</li>
    <li><strong>Device and Usage Data:</strong> We may collect anonymized device information and usage data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Collect Information</h2>
  <p>We collect data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Directly from you when you upload content or enter trip details.</li>
    <li>Automatically through usage of the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use your data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide app features like uploading and sharing trips.</li>
    <li>Allow collaboration between users.</li>
    <li>Improve the app through usage insights.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All user data and media uploads are stored using <strong>Google Firebase Firestore</strong>.</p>

  <h2>5. Sharing of Information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>With users you invite to your trips.</li>
    <li>With Firebase and other service providers necessary to operate the app.</li>
    <li>With legal authorities if required by law.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We currently do not implement additional security measures beyond those provided by Firebase. Please use caution when uploading sensitive content.</p>

